  "str_1094": "<h2 style=\"font-size:1rem;font-weight:800;color:var(--text-secondary);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.06em\">🎯 6-Month Target KPIs</h2>",
  "str_1095": "HIV Tests Distributed",
  "str_1096": "USSD Sessions (*775#)",
  "str_1097": "Peer Agents Trained",
  "str_1098": "Pilot Districts",
  "str_1099": "Negotiation Module Views",
  "str_1100": "Within Grant Budget",
  "str_1101": "📌 <strong>Why 2 districts first?</strong> Starting in Gasabo (urban) and Huye (rural) allows direct comparison of urban vs. rural uptake, USSD usage patterns, and peer agent effectiveness. Success data from these districts forms the evidence base for nationwide scaling in Phase 2. This is the most resource-efficient approach to demonstrating proof of concept within a single grant cycle.",
